Hugh Graham Belsey, MBE, (born May 1954) is a British art historian who is an authority on the art of Thomas Gainsborough. For 23 years he was the curator of Gainsborough's House in Sudbury. He is currently compiling a catalogue raisonn√© of Gainsborough's portraits which is scheduled for publication in 2018 by the Paul Mellon Centre for Studies in British Art.
